    <a style="font-weight:bold" href="/user/show/10051075-abhinav">Abhinav</a>

      
<span id="freeTextContainer11274699123779882913"><i>Michael wrote: &quot;Outstanding review. I must get over my squeamishness about magical realism. As you say, a few ghosts and speaking over distance should</i></span>
  <span id="freeText11274699123779882913" style="display:none"><i>Michael wrote: "Outstanding review. I must get over my squeamishness about magical realism. As you say, a few ghosts and speaking over distance shouldn't spoil the realistic portrait of cultures and worthwhile l..."</i><br /><br />Thank you Michael. I'm glad you like the review. :)<br /><br />I've realised I quite enjoy magical realism (Life of Pi &amp; Rushdie's The Enchantress of Florence) &amp; this book too has its fair share of that element. Besides, Rushdie's grand vision in this novel ensures that those leaps across time &amp; distance are effortless - I was simply enthralled.<br /><br />I'll definitely check out the one you mentioned. Hope you like Shalimar the Clown. And Happy New Year!</span>
  <a data-text-id="11274699123779882913" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

    <br/>

    <span class="xhrCommentFooter greyText">
      Jan 01, 2014 08:48AM
    </span>

